OL,6,FTal Spiegel, for Smith, told the court
OL,7,Fin mitigation that his client suffered
OL,8,Fhealth problems and was living an
OL,9,Fisolated lifestyle "sat in front of
OL,10,Fthe TV".
OL,12,FAt the time of the messages, he had
OL,13,Fbecome interested in the war in Gaza,
OL,14,Fwith Mr Spiegel adding his client now
OL,15,Funderstood the "difference between
OL,16,Fbeing Israeli and Jewish".
OL,18,FMr Kitson said Smith should be jailed
OL,19,Ffor 10 weeks, but reduced this to
OL,20,Feight weeks upon mitigation.
